      "review_summary": "The PR trims blank `logging.file` values to the default rolling log path, emits a one-time stderr warning when file appends fail, and adds logging/config tests while tightening schema validation.\n\nPR surface: Source +9, Tests +102. Total +111 across 4 files.\n\nReproducibility: yes. Source inspection shows current main passes `cfg?.file` unchanged and ignores `appendLogLine()` false returns, and the PR body includes after-fix terminal proof; I did not run a mutable repro in this read-only checkout.",
